msgctxt "sn48.27:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.27:0.2"
msgid "3. Chaḷindriyavagga "
msgstr "3. The Six Faculties "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 27. Arahantasutta → arahatā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.27:0.3"
msgid "27. Arahantasutta "
msgstr "27. A Perfected One "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn48.27:1.1"
msgid "“Chayimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these six faculties. "

msgctxt "sn48.27:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cha? "
msgstr "What six? "

msgctxt "sn48.27:1.3"
msgid "Cakkhundriyaṃ, sotindriyaṃ, ghānindriyaṃ, jivhindriyaṃ, kāyindriyaṃ, manindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "The faculties of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn48.27:1.4"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imesaṃ channaṃ indriyānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto hoti—"
msgstr "A mendicant comes to be freed by not grasping after truly understanding these six faculties’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.27:1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto’”ti. "
msgstr "Such a mendicant is called a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.27:1.6"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

